Poland Says KGHM Plan to Take Over Quadra ‘Interesting Idea’

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i
-- 
2011-12-06T16:08:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-06/poland-says-kghm-plan-to-take-over-quadra-interesting-idea-1-.html
KGHM Polska Miedz SA (KGH) ’s plan to buy
Canada’s  Quadra FNX Mining Ltd. (QUX)  is an “interesting idea,”
Maciej Wewior, a spokesman for the Treasury Ministry, said by
phone today.  The ministry, KGHM’s biggest shareholder with a 32 percent
stake, will look “closely” at the transaction, Wewior said.  KGHM, Poland’s sole copper and silver producer, has already
received all necessary approvals from its corporate structures,
Dariusz Wyborski, a spokesman for the company, said by phone
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pawel Kozlowski in Warsaw at 
 pkozlowski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
